'''鋸針蟻屬''' ('''''Odontomachus''''' ) 隸屬[[蟻科|蟻科]][[針蟻亞科|針蟻亞科]]，棲息於[[熱帶|熱帶]]和[[亞熱帶|亞熱帶]]，為肉食性。

鋸針蟻屬具有[[觸發式大顎|觸發式大顎]] (trap-jaw)，大顎能以極快的速度關上，以捕捉獵物或是透過反作用力彈飛自己躲避敵人。
==總覽==
鋸針蟻屬英文俗名''trap-jaw ants'' ，鋸針蟻屬有一對發達的大顎，打開的角度可達180度。大顎可以透過內部的結構固定在打開的姿勢，大顎的內部生有一對用來感知的板機毛 (trigger-hair)，當獵物觸碰到板機毛 (trigger-hair) 時大顎便會快速關上，大顎強而有力，且運動速度極快，鋸針蟻屬的英文俗名便是由此而來，大顎命中獵物時會殺死或使獵物殘廢。如果大顎沒有命中目標，鋸針蟻屬可以重複地固定大顎、擊發大顎，除此之外，鋸針蟻屬也可以像其他螞蟻一樣正常開闔大顎。鋸針蟻屬也會利用大顎來擊飛敵人，或是彈飛自己以躲避敵人<ref name="TrapJawPatek">{{cite journal|title=Multifunctionality and mechanical origins: Ballistic jaw propulsion in trap-jaw ants|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/103/34/12787.full.pdf+html|date=22 August 2006|journal=[[Proceedings_of_the_National_Academy_of_Sciences|Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]]|accessdate=7 June 2008|issue=34|doi=10.1073/pnas.0604290103|volume=103|pages=12787–12792|format=[[Portable_Document_Format|PDF]]|pmc=1568925|pmid=16924120|vauthors=Patek SN, Baio JE, Fisher BL, Suarez AV|archive-date=2014-08-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140831131730/http://www.pnas.org/content/103/34/12787.full.pdf+html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.berkeley.edu/news/media/releases/2006/08/21_ant_video.shtml Ant Jaws Break Speed Record] {{Wayback|url=http://www.berkeley.edu/news/media/releases/2006/08/21_ant_video.shtml |date=20210117211610 }} — Videos of ''Odontomachus'' jumping using its jaws</ref>。[[Image:OdontomachusHeadWheeler.jpg|thumb]]

鋸針蟻屬的幼蟲外形特殊<ref>{{Cite web|title=Weird Ants Have Hairy Blobs for Babies|url=https://www.livescience.com/59062-trap-jaw-ants-have-hairy-baby-blobs.html|last=Pappas|first=Stephanie|last2=May 11|first2=Live Science Contributor {{!}}|website=Live Science|access-date=2019-06-28|last3=ET|first3=2017 07:41am|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130132258/https://www.livescience.com/59062-trap-jaw-ants-have-hairy-baby-blobs.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，其身體上生有長長的肉脊，且其背部生有黏著墊，可以用來黏在蟻巢的牆壁上<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Larvae of trap-jaw ants, Odontomachus Latreille, 1804 (Hymenoptera: Formicidae): morphology and biological notes|url=https://myrmecologicalnews.org/cms/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&id=1481&Itemid=407|last=Fox|first=E.G.P.|last2=Smith|first2=A.A.|date=2017|journal=The Austrian Society of Entomofaunistics|doi=10.25849/myrmecol.news_025:017|last3=Gibson|first3=J.C.|last4=Solis|first4=D.R.|access-date=2020-03-06|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225050712/https://myrmecologicalnews.org/cms/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&id=1481&Itemid=407|dead-url=no}}</ref>。幼蟲為肉食性，幼蟲會蛻皮三次<ref name=":0" />，幼蟲會利用其他介質結繭<ref>{{Cite web|title=How Trap-Jaw Ants Develop From Larvae Stages [Watch]|url=https://www.sciencetimes.com/articles/14775/20170510/how-trap-jaw-ants-develop-from-larvae-stages-watch.htm|date=2017-05-10|language=en|website=Science Times|access-date=2019-06-28|archive-date=2019-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628211950/https://www.sciencetimes.com/articles/14775/20170510/how-trap-jaw-ants-develop-from-larvae-stages-watch.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==大顎運動的速度==
鋸針蟻屬大顎運動的速度是動物界中第二快的<ref name="TrapJawPatek" />，第一快的是德古拉蟻 (''[[Mystrium|Mystrium]] camillae'' )<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dracula ants possess fastest known animal appendage: The snap-jaw|url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2018/12/181211192143.htm|website=ScienceDaily|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108105438/https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2018/12/181211192143.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有研究指出 ''[[Odontomachus_bauri|Odontomachus bauri]]''  大顎運動的速度介於時速 126 ~ 230 公里。大顎關上的時間平均為 130 微秒。加速度可達 1 000 000 m/s²。

==擬態==
''[[Enoplomischus|Enoplomischus]]'' 屬的跳蛛會擬態成鋸針蟻屬<ref name="Wesolowska_2005">{{cite journal|title=A new species of ''Enoplomischus'' from Kenya (Araneae: Salticidae: Leptorchestinae)|url=http://www.biol.uni.wroc.pl/cassidae/Enoplomischus%20spinosus.pdf|last=Wesołowska|first=W.|date=2005|journal=Genus|issue=2|volume=16|pages=307–311|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070315221403/http://www.biol.uni.wroc.pl/cassidae/Enoplomischus%20spinosus.pdf|archivedate=2007-03-15|url-status=dead}}</ref>。

==分布==
鋸針蟻屬分布於中南美洲、亞洲、澳洲與非洲<ref name="Schmidt&Shattuck_2014">{{cite journal|title=The Higher Classification of the Ant Subfamily Ponerinae (Hymenoptera: Formicidae), with a Review of Ponerine Ecology and Behavior|last=Schmidt|first=C. A.|last2=Shattuck|first2=S. O.|date=2014|journal=[[Zootaxa|Zootaxa]]|issue=1|doi=10.11646/zootaxa.3817.1.1|volume=3817|pages=1–242|pmid=24943802}}</ref>。有研究指出在美國「''Odontomachus haematodus'' 1956年在阿拉巴馬州被記錄到，但近期研究者指出該物種已沿著墨西哥灣散播，最遠至佛羅里達州的彭薩科拉<ref>{{cite web|title=Powerful Trap-jaw Ants are Gaining Ground in the Southeastern United States|url=http://entomologytoday.org/2014/06/20/powerful-trap-jaw-ants-are-gaining-ground-in-the-southeastern-united-states/|accessdate=20 June 2014|date=20 June 2014|publisher=Entomology Today|quote=One species called ''Odontomachus haematodu''s was unofficially recorded in Alabama back in 1956. But now researchers have officially confirmed that the species has spread across the Gulf Coast, at least as far east as Pensacola, Florida.|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128082624/https://entomologytoday.org/2014/06/20/powerful-trap-jaw-ants-are-gaining-ground-in-the-southeastern-united-states/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。」Magdalena Sorger則指出，「在過去，''Odontomachus ruginodis'' 的分布範圍被認為侷限在奧蘭多地區，而近期有一筆 ''O''. ''ruginodis'' 的紀錄出現在奧蘭多北邊超過100英里處，位於佛羅里達州的蓋恩斯維爾<ref>{{cite web|title=Powerful Trap-jaw Ants are Gaining Ground in the Southeastern United States|url=http://entomologytoday.org/2014/06/20/powerful-trap-jaw-ants-are-gaining-ground-in-the-southeastern-united-states/|accessdate=20 June 2014|date=20 June 2014|publisher=Entomology Today|quote=As recently as a few years ago, another species called ''Odontomachus ruginodis'' was thought to be confined to the Orlando region, and points south. But now Sorger has confirmed a record of ''ruginodis'' more than a hundred miles north of Orlando, in Gainesville, Florida.|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128082624/https://entomologytoday.org/2014/06/20/powerful-trap-jaw-ants-are-gaining-ground-in-the-southeastern-united-states/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。」而 ''Odontomachus relictus'' 則只在佛羅里達中部發現，棲息於長有灌木叢的沙脊地形中<ref>{{cite web|title=Powerful Trap-jaw Ants are Gaining Ground in the Southeastern United States|url=http://entomologytoday.org/2014/06/20/powerful-trap-jaw-ants-are-gaining-ground-in-the-southeastern-united-states/|accessdate=20 June 2014|date=20 June 2014|publisher=Entomology Today|quote=Not all of the trap-jaw species are on the move, however. Sorger also studies ''Odontomachus relictus'', a species that is found only in endangered scrub habitat on central Florida’s ancient sand ridges.|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128082624/https://entomologytoday.org/2014/06/20/powerful-trap-jaw-ants-are-gaining-ground-in-the-southeastern-united-states/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

